alerts.description: Continuous heavy rainfall caused by a low-pressure area may result in localized flooding in Roxas City, particularly in coastal barangays and urban areas with poor drainage.
Light to moderate rains due to the Northeast Monsoon may cause minor flooding in Ormoc City, particularly in barangays near creeks and rivers.
Heavy rains brought by a tropical storm are expected to cause flooding in Narra, particularly in low-lying barangays and agricultural areas near rivers.
Heavy rains due to a tropical disturbance are expected to cause flash flooding in Mandaue City. Low-lying urban areas and areas with poor drainage are at high risk.
Heavy rains from a tropical disturbance are likely to cause widespread flooding in Jolo, particularly in coastal and low-lying areas.
Heavy rains due to the Intertropical Convergence Zone (ITCZ) are expected to cause flooding in Compostela, especially in low-lying areas and barangays near the Agusan River.
